structured.title: Rachel Shares God First Audio Teaching Intro
structured.overview: The recording captures Rachel and the user refining and repeating an audio introduction for God First Church Barry teachings. They emphasize welcoming listeners to the "God First" audio teaching, hoping the messages help people in their journey with Jesus. The user adds a call to action, inviting listeners to visit the church website for more information. Rachel then speaks about Jesus comforting people in different ways, sometimes dramatically and sometimes quietly, and invites listeners who want to meet with Jesus to respond by holding out their hands where they are.

apps_results.content:
## Introduction to God First teaching
- Audio teaching from God First Church Barry  
- Aim: help listeners’ journey with Jesus  
- Website: godfirstchurchbarry.com for info and joining  

## Purpose of the teaching
- Teaching intended to strengthen faith in Christ  
- Repeated welcome to all accessing the teaching  
- Focus on ongoing spiritual growth with Jesus  

## Encouragement and promise
- Reference to God’s promise: every tear wiped away  
- Acknowledges both dramatic and quiet encounters with Jesus  
- No single “right” way to experience God’s presence  

## Invitation to respond
- Invitation to meet with Jesus personally  
- Practical step: put hands out in front to respond  
- Emphasis on openness to Jesus wherever you are  

## Next steps
- Visit godfirstchurchbarry.com to learn or join  
- Continue listening to teaching for faith growth  
- Personally respond in prayer and openness to Jesus
